text: Nazitamak () is a rural locality (a village) in Asyanovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 137 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 13 km from Dyurtyuli, 1 km from Asyanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Nazitamak
